I imagine you could do even better with something like PostSharp or Fody.<p><pre><code>    public void MyFunction([InRange(0, 5)] int x, [NotNull] object y)
    {
        // ...
    }
</code></pre>
I just checked, and in fact Fody can do something just like this [1].<p>The only downside I see is contracts like this would be hard to write concisely:<p><pre><code>    if (useFirstObject == true)
        Contract.AssertNotNull(firstObject);
    else
        Contract.AssertNotNull(secondObject);
</code></pre>
[1] <a href="https://github.com/Fody/NullGuard" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/Fody/NullGuard</a>
